Collections API - These are Ready-made data structures + algorithms to store and manipulate the data.
                - it provides flexibility

Why Collections API - without collections we use [int a[] = new int[5]; ] traditional arrays
                    - problem was - fixed size
                                  - no built in methods (searching, sorting)
                                  - can store only one type data (primitive array)
                                  - hard to manage dynamic data





